article.headline: Wisconsin 76, S. Dakota 61
article.story: MADISON, Wis. -- Jon Leuer scored a career-high 29 points and Jordan Taylor narrowly missed the first triple double in Wisconsin history as the Badgers beat South Dakota 76-61 on Saturday. Taylor finished with 20 points, 11 rebounds and nine assists. The Coyotes (3-5) largely played a zone defense, which initially didn't look like a good decision. The Badgers (6-2) led by as much as 15 points in the first half as the Badgers hit seven of their first 10 3-point tries, including four from Leuer. But Wisconsin struggled from long distance after that and South Dakota was able to claw back to trail 42-37 at half. From there, Wisconsin held the lead but could never really shake the Coyotes. With less than 8 minutes left in the game, South Dakota trailed 57-51 but could pull no closer. Charlie Westbrook led South Dakota with 18 points.
